Date:  15/3/1851
Source:  Lyttelton Times
Author:
Vol / Page:  6
Edition:
Quote:  Massacre Bay Coal is a species of anthracite, and when burned in a crucible under the reducing flame of the blowpipe, gives the following results: - Ignition slow and difficult; flame feeble, yellowish not persistent, much smoke and strong sulphurous odour: no traces of bituminous matter, or inflamable volatile gases observed.
